<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-06-21T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-06-21T09:00:00-05:00" n="809" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">690.419/6–2149: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Douglas</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-06-21T15:00:00+01:00">June 21,
                                    1949—3 p. m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received June 21—10:09 a. m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2390. For Gay,<note n="43" xml:id="d809fn43">Merrill C. Gay, Assistant
                                Chief of the Division of Commercial Policy.</note> CP, and
                                Bell,<note n="44" xml:id="d809fn44">George L. Bell, Associate
                                Director of the Office of International Trade, Department of
                                Commerce.</note> OIT, from Martin and McIntyre. First session with
                            British today resulted satisfactory exploration problems involved
                            application export controls China.</p>
                        <p>Session tomorrow considering detailof commodity and country coverage. We
                            require soonest Washington suggestions selected list key 1B items
                            essential for prompt UK control.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Douglas</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>